<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Head completely dark reddish brown (red in alive specimen; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 17–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 17 - 19. 17 habitus of holotype. ♀ Megischus kuafu Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. (except ovipositor and ovipositor sheath) 18 ovipositor and ovipositor sheath 19 collecting living specimen." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1022.62833.figures17-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/517765" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">19</figureCitation>
), temples slightly bulging behind eyes; ocellar area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–5" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 5. Megischus kuafu Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 1 head, frontal view 2 head, dorsal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view 5 mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1022.62833.figures1-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/517761" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2</figureCitation>
) transversely rugose; vertex reticulate-rugose medially, followed by weakly transverse rugae posteriorly almost reaching occipital carina; pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–5" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 5. Megischus kuafu Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 1 head, frontal view 2 head, dorsal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view 5 mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1022.62833.figures1-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/517761" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">4</figureCitation>
) subparallel anteriorly and with distinct pronotal fold; apical median portion of neck shiny (before protonal fold); medio-anterior pronotum moderately wide (in dorsal view) and strong transverse rugae; scutellum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 6–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 6 - 8. Megischus kuafu Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 6 mesoscutum and scutellum, dorsal view 7 propodeum, dorsal view 8 wings." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1022.62833.figures6-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/517762" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">6</figureCitation>
) almost glabrous and with foveolae laterally; vein 1-M ca 5.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as vein 1-SR; hind basitarsus densely setose and parallel-sided, ventral length 7.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
maximum width.
</paragraph>
